
[1]steeple

   STEEPLE, n. A turret of a church, ending in a point; a spire. It
   differs from a tower, which usually ends in a square form, thought the
   name is sometimes given to a tower. The bell of a church is usually
   hung in the steeple.

   They, far from steeples and their sacred sound---
